name: "Chinese" Garage
description: A Grade II listed motor garage and petrol station built in the style of a Japanese pagoda in 1928. Now a Tesco Express.
address: Chinese Garage, Stone Park Avenue, BR3 3FE

name: Altab Ali Park
description: Altab Ali Park was renamed in 1998 after a murdered 25-year-old Bangladeshi Sylheti clothing worker. Formerly known as St. Mary's Park, it is the site of the old 14 C white church, St. Mary Matfelon which gave Whitechapel its name.

name: Battersea Exchange
description: Battersea Exchange creates 290 new homes, 21% of which are affordable, a new two-form entry primary school and around 4000 sqm of commercial space for shops, offices and restaurants, as well as a new entrance to Queenstown Road Station.
address: 177 Battersea Park Rd, Nine Elms, SW8 4LR

name: Fish Island Village
description: Fish Island Village is a major new live-work neighbourhood in east London - a mid-rise development comprising 588 mixed tenure dwellings with 5,522m² commercial space delivered by The Trampery as a campus for sustainable fashion businesses.

name: Fore Street Art Trail
description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
address: Fore Street, Angel Edmonton, Enfield, N18 2UE

name: Hyde Park Chapel
description: The four-story Church façade and prominent seven-story tower is covered in Portland stone and highlighted by a golden steeple. The interior features the Christus statue and a large mural of the resurrected Jesus Christ.

name: New Ground (online only)
description: 25 homes designed with the Older Women’s Co-Housing group using PTE’s ‘fabric first’ approach which maximises the benefits of orientation, air-tightness, insulation and following the co-housing model. www.youtube.com/watch?v=9q25nbEl8rg

name: Pushkin House
description: The independent cultural centre Pushkin House will contribute to this year's Open House Festival through a programme of events and community initiatives at its Grade-II listed building in Bloomsbury Square.

name: Site Report Book Launch at Flat Time House
description: Theatrum Mundi invites you to the launch of a new book - Site Report by Glasgow-based artist and poet Rhona Warwick Paterson. The book will launch with an event at Flat Time House, former home studio of conceptual artist John Latham.
